    <div id="connect" class="section scrollspy" style="margin-top: 50px">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col s1"></div>
            <div class="col s5">
                <h4>How to contact co-workers:</h4>
                <h5>Channels</h5>
                <p>There are 2 types of channels, public and private. You can tell if a channel is public by the "<strong>#</strong>" next to the name. Public means that anyone can be added or request to be added to the channel. If a channel has a <strong>lock</strong> icon, the channel is private. Private means that the people in that channel were by invitation ONLY.</p>

                <p>Different channels are used for different conversations. For example, the <strong>#academics</strong> channel is used to contact everyone who falls in the department of “Academics” but <strong>#academic-recruitment</strong> would be used to talk to those who fall in “Academics” but under the category “Recruitment” as well.</p>

                <p>Channels are created by administration.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col s5"><img class="rightContent materialboxed" alt="Connect with Co-Workers" src="/img/slack1.png"></div>
            <div class="col s1"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!--row3-->
    <div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col s1"></div>
            <div class="col s5">
                <h5>Direct Messages</h5>
                <p>If you don’t need to talk to the whole channel and just need to talk to either an individual or a few individuals, you can use direct messages. Just add the name of those you need to chat with by clicking the “+” next to “Direct Messages” to create your own chat-room.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col s5"><img class="rightContent materialboxed" alt="Direct Message" src="/img/slack2.png"></div>
            <div class="col s1"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!--row4-->
    <div id="ping" class="section scrollspy" style="margin-top: 50px">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col s1"></div>
            <div class="col s5">
                <h4>How to notify team members (pinging a team member):</h4>
                <p><strong>@channel</strong>: This is used to ping all team members in the channel whether they are online or not. We try to keep this at a minimum during odd hours of the day/night (8pm-7am EST) as to not disturb those who are sleeping. Please be considerate when using this ping!</p>

                <p><strong>@here</strong>: This is used to ping team members in the channel that are currently online. </p>

                <p><strong>@[insert-specific name here]</strong>: This is used to ping a specific team member in the channel. </p>

                <p>Use these different pings to get team member’s attention if you have an urgent task or announcement or - if you need to get someone’s attention.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col s5"><img class="rightContent materialboxed" alt="Pinging Team" src="/img/slack3.png"></div>
            <div class="col s1"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!--row5-->
    <div id="access" class="section scrollspy" style="margin-top: 50px">
